-- Springboks Select Five Uncapped Players for Tour; Habana Out
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2012-10-28T14:23:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-28/springboks-select-five-uncapped-players-for-tour-habana-out.html
South Africa  named five uncapped
players in its squad for a rugby tour of Britain and Ireland,
while winger  Bryan Habana  is out through injury.  Habana, South Africa’s all-time leading try-scorer, hurt
his knee playing for Western Province in yesterday’s Currie Cup
final victory over Natal Sharks. He joins players including
Pierre Spies, Frans Steyn and Schalk Burger on the sidelines
because of injury.  Wingers Lionel Mapoe and Raymond Rhule, loose forward Arno
Botha, lock Franco van der Merwe and scrum-half Jano Vermaak are
the new names in the squad.  The Springboks play their first Test against Ireland on
Nov. 10 before matches against Scotland and England on the
following Saturdays. The squad was announced on the  team’s
website .  South Africa squad: Alberts, Botha, Brits, Cilliers,
Coetzee, De Jongh,  De Villiers  (capt.), Du Plessis, Etzebeth,
Hougaard, Jantjies, Kirchner, Kruger, Lambie, Louw, Mapoe,
Mtawarira, Mvovo, Pienaar, Pietersen, Ralepelle, Rhule,
Steenkamp, Steyn, Strauss, Taute, Van der Linde, Flip van der
Merwe, Franco van der Merwe, Vermaak, Vermeulen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Peter-Joseph Hegarty in London at 
